headline: What Analysts Think Is Changing The Starbucks Turnaround Story Now
summary: Starbucks latest valuation update reflects a subtle but telling shift in expectations, with its fair value estimate inching up to about $94.19 per share even as the assumed discount rate edges higher to roughly 8.99%. While long term revenue growth is now modeled a bit lower, near term traffic improvements, steadier comps, and early progress on the turnaround are helping support a slightly richer intrinsic view despite ongoing macro and execution risks. Read on to see how these evolving...
